description:
firmware/bridge-zephyr/subsys/lichen/lora_l2.h line 78 states lichen_lora_l2_init() "May only be called once" but the implementation (lora_l2.c lines 144-147) is idempotent:

  if (atomic_get(&lora_state.initialized)) {
      return 0;
  }

Documentation should say "Idempotent: returns 0 if already initialized" to match actual behavior and the pattern used by lichen_lora_l2_start()/stop().
